rtford connecticut and received a ba in history from clark university in  and a jd from new york law school in  while in law school he worked as a clerk for the chief bankruptcy judge of the southern district of new york edward ryan careeredit after graduating from law school lasry took a position in the bankruptcy branch of the law firm angel  frankel together with his sister sonia gardner they founded amroc investments in  and avenue capital group in  one year later lasry became the director of the private debt department at the investment firm r d smith now smith vasillou management this is where lasry first got involved in trade claims he then took a position as codirector of the bankruptcy and corporate reorganization department at cowen  company there lasry recruited his sister sonia gardner also an attorney to assist in the companys trade claims department lasry left cowen  company and joined the robert m bass group focused on distressed security investments in  lasry and his sister founded the firm amroc investments with  million in seed money from various investors amroc purchased both trade claims and bank debt held by vendors of bankrupt andor distressed companies in  lasry and gardner invested  million of their own capital and founded the avenue capital group which initially focused on distressed debt and special situations primarily in the united states the partners successfully expanded the firms investment focus to europe and asia the two went on to build their hedge fund which had as much as  billion in assets under management in  lasry was considered for the position of us ambassador to france but declined consideration for business reasons in  forbes listed lasry as one of the  highestearning hedge fund managers in  with total earnings of  million in april  lasry became coowner of the nbas milwaukee bucks after purchasing the team from herb kohl for  million following the  us election lasry and the milwaukee bucks became one of three nba teams to openly state they would not be staying at trump branded hotels when on the road  lasry is a member of kappa beta phi lasry is a major democratic party donor philanthropyedit in  lasry and his wife contributed support to the university of pennsylvania and cochaired the penn parent leadership committee in  they donated  million to clark university for the construction of the “cathy  and marc  lasry center for bioscience” lasry served as a director of the nd street y and the big apple circus and was a trustee of the mount sinai hospital manhattan he is a prominent donor to democratic party causes in january  lasry participated in portfolios with purpose an annual stock selection contest in which participants pick portfolios on behalf of their favorite charities personal lifeedit lasry is married to cathy cohen and has five children his son alexander worked for white house senior adviser valerie jarrett lasrys daughter samantha was a staffer for congressman rahm emanuel lasrys hobbies include basketball tennis and comics notesedit  httpgawkercomfhappybirthday  forbes the worlds billionaires mark lasry march   a b wee gillian feb   lasry sees europe bankruptcy bonanza as bad debts obscure assets bloomberg retrieved may     tablet magazine the next owner of ‘newsweek’ will be jewish – a plea against one of the candidates by marc tracy july    a b c bloomberg lasry sees europe bankruptcy bonanza as bad debts obscure assets february    ahuja maneet the alpha masters unlocking the genius of the worlds top hedge funds hoboken nj wiley p  isbn    a b c d new york law school alumni bulletin spotlight luncheon a conversation with marc lasry  retrieved june    a b c ahuja maneet the alpha masters  unlocking the genius of the worlds top hedge funds hoboken nj wiley pp – isbn    tausche kayla april   why lasry said non merci retrieved june     vardi nathan february   the  highestearning hedge fund managers and traders forbes   nba owners approve sale of bucks to edens lasry  kwesi m